# Crystal Theme & Tournament Dialogue

Tournament-related UI must follow the shared design contract. Do not invent layout, status, or accent colors inline.

## Sources of truth

- Colors: `frontend/src/theme/crystal.ts` + CSS vars in `frontend/src/index.css`
- Tailwind: use `crystal-*` tokens (and existing `brand-*` aliases that map to Crystal)
- Tournament rules: `frontend/src/theme/tournament.dialogue.ts` (`tournamentDialogue`)

## Required patterns

1. Import `tournamentDialogue` (or `gameAccent` / `statusDialogue`) for page shells, surfaces, typography, CTAs, filters, and status badges.
2. New tournament pages must use `tournamentDialogue.page.shell` (or `shellNarrow`).
3. Status badges must use `tournamentDialogue.status` / `statusDialogue(status)` — never hardcode LIVE / UPCOMING labels or colors.
4. Card hero gradients must come from `gameAccent(game)` or `tournamentDialogue.accentVariants` — never raw hex or one-off gradient class strings.
5. Prefer `crystal-primary`, `crystal-glow`, `crystal-deep`, `crystal-border`, `crystal-surface` over new ad-hoc colors.

## Do not

- Add purple/indigo or cream “AI default” palettes on tournament surfaces
- Duplicate status maps or page padding/title classes inside components
- Build tournament modals/cards that ignore the dialogue surface recipes
